cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OHG, please cite it as below."
title: "OHG: Ordered Hypergeometric (Minimum-Hypergeometric) Enrichment"
abstract: >-
  Ordered / minimum-hypergeometric (mHG) enrichment test for one ranked gene list
  against a collection of gene sets. Reports significance (a permutation-calibrated
  p-value), localization (cutoff rank and leading-edge fraction), and magnitude (a
  normalized leading-edge score) as three separate, never-pre-mixed axes.
